LIS3033
圖書館資訊系統
3
學士班
必修
4
鄭瑋



This new course continues and expands the former 3-credit required course, Library Automation. In this class, you will be introduced to the practices of systems librarianship as well as a wide array of computerized systems and technologies, including the integrated library systems (ILS) and information products and services that configure and support the public access computing and library staff work zones. You will also be introduced to the emerging technologies that are expanding and evolving the library services.




