LIS3037
檔案學導論
3
學士班
選修
資訊與文獻學研究議題
林奇秀



This 3-credit, undergraduate level course will introduce you to the basic operations and theoretical issues in modern archives administration. Archives are a social institution that preserves important individual and organizational records and manuscripts, which constitute the collective memory or a society. Archives and libraries are both memory organizations. They share many similarities in their operations and services. But they also differ in many aspects from the nature of the collected materials to the unique challenges in the digital age. This class is desiged to offer you an overview of the issues facing the archival profession.





